<TITLE> HC stays cases against Hannan Shah for 3 months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com) -- The High Court Wednesday stayed for three months two extortion cases against BNP chairperson's adviser ASM Hannan Shah and son Shah Rezaul Hannan. The court also asked the government to explain in four weeks why the two cases filed against them would not be quashed. The High Court bench of Justice Abdul Matin and Justice Abdul Hai passed the orders following appeals by Hannan and the son. Fisherman Moinuddin filed a case with Kapasia Police Station in Gazipur on May 12, accusing them of taking lease of a swamp by abusing power and also of extorting Tk 50,000. On May 13, Kapasia Degree College teacher Ruhul Amin filed another extortion case against Hannan, alleging that Hannan had taken Tk 2 lakh from him for reinstatement to his job. Barrister Rafique-ul Huq defended Hannan and his son in the court, which granted them bails on July 16. Hannan and his son were arrested on May 14 from their Mohakhali DOHS home. bd
